peopleAlsoAsk.question: What is the highest paid Banksy art?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Love Is In The Bin is both the only work of art ever to be created live at auction and the all-time highest selling Banksy, achieving almost £18.6 million when the original anonymous buyer (Sotheby's only disclosed that the pranked buyer was a "private European collector") returned it to auction in 2021.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: Why is Banksy's artwork so expensive?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Banksy – the elusive street artist whose works have captivated the world. But what is it about his art that makes it so valuable? From his mysterious identity to his limited edition pieces, Banksy's art is not only sought after for its aesthetic appeal but also for its political and social commentary.
